{"topicSections":[{"title":"Group","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSThemesOrangeBusinessTools\/documentation\/OUDSThemesOrangeBusinessTools\/OrangeBusinessToolsTheme"],"anchor":"Group"},{"title":"Classes","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSThemesOrangeBusinessTools\/documentation\/OUDSThemesOrangeBusinessTools\/OrangeBusinessToolsThemeColorChartSemanticTokensProvider"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Classes"},{"title":"Extended Modules","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSThemesOrangeBusinessTools\/documentation\/OUDSThemesOrangeBusinessTools\/Foundation"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Extended-Modules"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesOrangeBusinessTools\/documentation\/OUDSThemesOrangeBusinessTools"},"sections":[],"metadata":{"images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"ic_theme_orangebusinesstools.png"}],"role":"collection","symbolKind":"module","externalID":"OUDSThemesOrangeBusinessTools","title":"Theme Orange Business Tools","modules":[{"name":"Theme Orange Business Tools"}],"roleHeading":"Library"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The Orange Business Tools theme is dedicated to applications with strong dimensions constraints."}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/oudsthemesorangebusinesstools"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[[]]},"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"codeListing","code":["🧬 Theme version: 2.1.0"],"syntax":null},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Some products may have heavy and very rich user interfaces with a lot of components and elements to display and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with which users can interact. Thus for such products there are specific constraints of dimensions, spaces and sizes.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"That is the reason why this theme exists.","type":"text"}]},{"style":"note","type":"aside","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This theme is related to Orange theme module to use some raw tokens of colors."}]}]},{"style":"note","type":"aside","name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It contains also colors dedicated to charts."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"style":"important","type":"aside","name":"Important","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Orange Business Tools theme is read-only: it cannot be suclassed or derivated."}]}]},{"type":"heading","text":"How to use the theme","anchor":"How-to-use-the-theme","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can use "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesOrangeBusinessTools\/documentation\/OUDSThemesOrangeBusinessTools\/OrangeBusinessToolsTheme"},{"type":"text","text":" directly. To use the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesOrangeBusinessTools\/documentation\/OUDSThemesOrangeBusinessTools\/OrangeBusinessToolsTheme"},{"type":"text","text":" without further modifications, you will have to use the "},{"code":"OUDSThemeableView","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for your root view and give it an instance of "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesOrangeBusinessTools\/documentation\/OUDSThemesOrangeBusinessTools\/OrangeBusinessToolsTheme"},{"type":"text","text":". Keep in mind the themes are "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Swift class objects"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and can be heavy, so you may use only as instance as singleton and not store any properties."}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["@main","struct YourApp: App {","    var body: some Scene {","        WindowGroup {","            OUDSThemeableView(theme: OrangeBusinessToolsTheme()) {","                \/\/ Your root view","            }","        }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Then, in your views, you can simply use the theme through an environment variable to get the tokens:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["struct SomeView: View {","","    \/\/ Get OUDS environment variable for theme thanks to themeable view","    @Environment(\\.theme) var theme","    ","    var body: some View {","        ","        \/\/ Use the theme to retrieve the tokens","        \/\/ For spaces: theme.spaces","        \/\/ For sizes: theme.sizes","        \/\/ For borders: theme.borders","        \/\/ For elevations: theme.elevations","        \/\/ For opacities: theme.opacities","        \/\/ For colors: theme.colors","        \/\/ For button configuration: theme.button","        \/\/ For link configuration: theme.link","        \/\/ Etc.","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This theme embeds and registers the fonts for the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Orange Business Tools"},{"type":"text","text":" theme, you just need to use the theme object as is."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Tunable-theme","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Tunable theme"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The theme can be tuned with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Tuning"},{"type":"text","text":" object to give at init."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Some tuning object exists."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["\/\/ Define your theme tuning","let tuning = Tuning(hasRoundedButtons: true, hasRoundedTextInputs: true)","","\/\/ Apply it to your theme","let theme = OrangeBusinessToolsTheme(tuning: tuning)","\/\/ Or in one line","let theme = OrangeBusinessToolsTheme(tuning: Tuning(hasRoundedButtons: true, hasRoundedTextInputs: true))","","\/\/ Or apply predefined tunings","let orangeFranceTheme = OrangeBusinessToolsTheme(tuning: Tuning.OrangeFrance)","let orangeBusinessTheme = OrangeBusinessToolsTheme(tuning: Tuning.OrangeBusiness)","let maxitTheme = OrangeBusinessToolsTheme(tuning: Tuning.MaxIt)"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A default tuning is applied for this theme:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Tunable elements"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Default values","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"rounded corners buttons","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"❌ false","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"rounded corners text inputs","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ true"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]],"type":"table","header":"row"},{"anchor":"Typography","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Typography"},{"anchor":"Helvetica-Neue","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Helvetica Neue"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The Orange theme uses ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"Helvetica Neue","type":"text"}]},{"text":" typography. This font is already available through iOS.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It is possible to use another typography, by the ones recommended are the ones defined in tokens.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["\/\/ The three following instanciations are the same","let theme = OrangeBusinessToolsTheme()","let theme = OrangeBusinessToolsTheme(family: OrangeBrandFontRawTokens.familyBrandDefault)","let theme = OrangeBusinessToolsTheme(family: \"HelveticaNeue\") \/\/ Which is PostScript name of the font","","\/\/ This instanciation won't work as the font family is not recognised","let theme = OrangeBusinessToolsTheme(family: \"Helvetica Neue\")"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Other-fonts","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Other fonts"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"However if, in very particular cases, you need to use another font family, you can try using it by changing the value in the theme init."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["\/\/ Supposing you want to use another font:","\/\/ - like the Luciole font (https:\/\/luciole-vision.com\/) (very good for accessibility)","\/\/ - or the Roboto font (https:\/\/fonts.google.com\/specimen\/Roboto) (to support cyrillic alphabet)","\/\/ - or hevletica Neue Arabic (for arabic alphabet Helvetica flavoured)","\/\/ 1. Add the TTF files in your project","    ","\/\/ 2. Register the fonts with, for example, the function below","private func registerFonts() {","    let fonts = Bundle.main.urls(forResourcesWithExtension: \"ttf\", subdirectory: nil)","    fonts?.forEach { CTFontManagerRegisterFontsForURL($0 as CFURL, .process, nil) }","}","","\/\/ 3. At theme init, given the font family name, add it to the theme.","\/\/ Keep in mind that it might not work because PostScript name is used combining","\/\/ font family name and font weight.","\/\/ For Luciole font, use \"Luciole\", for Roboto font, use \"Roboto\", etc.","let theme = OrangeBusinessToolsTheme(family: theFontFamilyNameInPostScript)"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Specific rules to compute PostScript value are defined in "},{"code":"PostScriptFontNamesMap.swift","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If your font family is not well managed, you can "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios\/issues"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Tip","type":"aside","style":"tip"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For production products and official tools, ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Helvetica Neue","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" is preferred and should be used","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Important","type":"aside","style":"important"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If for your needs Helvetica Neue is not relevant (because does not support cyrilic, or not enough accessible, or not aligned with your needs), ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios\/discussions"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Tip","type":"aside","style":"tip"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For ecodesign principles you should challenge the use of fonts because they can increase the needed storage of your apps"}]}],"name":"Caution","type":"aside","style":"note"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Always check the license and terms of uses of the font your are using (distribution, hsoting, usage for comemrcial things, etc.)"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Important","type":"aside","style":"important"},{"anchor":"How-to-enrich-the-theme","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"How to enrich the theme"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You cannot derivate the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"Orange Business Tools","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" theme."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"How-it-looks-like","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"How it looks like"},{"anchor":"Actions","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Actions"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/images\/OUDSComponents\/component_button_OrangeBusinessTools.png","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Controls","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Controls"},{"anchor":"Checkboxes","level":4,"type":"heading","text":"Checkboxes"},{"tabs":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/images\/OUDSComponents\/component_checkbox_OrangeBusinessTools.png"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"title":"Checkbox"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/images\/OUDSComponents\/componen